## Summary

| Bug | Root Cause | Fix |
|-----|-----------|-----|
| **Duplicate processing** | Race condition in `dequeue()`: the `await asyncio.sleep(0.01)` between checking status and updating it allowed multiple workers to claim the same job | Move status change to `"processing"` before the `await` |
| **Vanishing failures** | Exception handler in worker only logged errors but never called `queue.fail()` to update job status | Add `queue.fail(job["id"], str(e))` call |

Public method signatures remain unchanged as required.
